Given the undirected dynamic graph with the edges provided, we can scan each edge and collect the time t whenever node 8 and node 3 are connected.

We start by initializing two sets, one for node 8 and one for node 3:
```css
set_8 = {0, 1, 3, 5, 6, 7, 8, 19, 20, 21, 24, 25, 26, 28, 29}
set_3 = {0, 1, 3, 5, 6, 7, 8, 19, 20, 21, 24, 25, 26, 28, 29}
```
We then iterate over all edges and check if the two nodes are connected:
```css
for edge in edges:
    u, v, t = edge
    if u in set_8 and v in set_3:
        set_8.remove(u)
        set_3.remove(v)
        if t == 1:
            print("Answer:", 1)
            break
        elif t == 3:
            print("Answer:", 3)
            break
```
